 complete the form to have a company restored\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form 208a, guidance notes’ (PDF, 437KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Send your completed form to the nearest county court to the company&rsquo;s registered office that deals with bankruptcy (select &lsquo;County Court&rsquo; under &lsquo;Search by court type&rsquo; in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/\" title=\"Her Majesty’s Courts &amp; Tribunal Service\">court finder</a>), or the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/Search.do?court_id=716\" title=\"Royal Courts of Justice\">Royal Courts of Justice.</a></p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also need to include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the court fee (cash, postal order or cheque made payable to Her Majesty’s Courts &amp; Tribunal Service)</li>\n  <li>a witness statement, containing the supporting information outlined in section 4 of the Treasury Solicitor&rsquo;s guide to company restoration</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>See the &lsquo;guide to company restoration&rsquo; for information about restoring a company.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.tsol.gov.uk/Publications/Scheme_Publications/company_restoration_Oct_2011.pdf\" title=\"How to apply to have a company restored\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Guide to company restoration’ (PDF, 624KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>In Scotland</h3>\n\n<p>Apply to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.scotcourts.gov.uk/locations/index.asp?crt=sup_cos&amp;val=contact\" title=\"Contact details for Scottish Court of Session\">Court of Session</a> if initial value of the company&rsquo;s shares that have been paid for (&lsquo;paid-up capital&rsquo;) is more than £120,000.</p>\n\n<p>For other companies, apply to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.scotcourts.gov.uk/locations/index.asp\" title=\"Scottish court locations\">local sheriff court.</a></p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll then have to serve a &lsquo;petition to restore&rsquo; on the Registrar of Companies in Scotland, and any other bodies the court asks you to.</p>\n\n<h3>In Northern Ireland</h3>\n\n<p>Apply by serving an &lsquo;originating summons&rsquo; on the Royal Courts of Justice:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nRoyal Courts of Justice\n<br />Chichester Street\n<br />Belfast \n<br />BT1 3JY\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<p>You also need to send this to the Registrar of Companies in Northern Ireland, along with a witness statement in support of the application.</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nThe Registrar of Companies\n<br />Companies House\n<br />Second Floor\n<br />The Linenhall\n<br />32-38 Linenhall Street\n<br />Belfast \n<br />BT2 8BG\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Applying for court order restoration is complicated. You should <a href=\"http://www.lawsociety.org.uk/choosingandusing/findasolicitor.law\" title=\"find a solicitor on the Law Society website\" rel=\"external\">get legal advice</a> before applying.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>What happens next</h2>\n\n<p>If your claim is accepted, the court will issue an Order to restore the company - you&rsquo;ll be sent this, and you must send it on to the Registrar of Companies. Once they have it they will restore the company.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll then need to take further action to try and get your money:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>get a &lsquo;judgment&rsquo; from court for the amount of the money you&rsquo;re owed together with interest and costs</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/statutory-demands\" title=\"Issue a statutory demand\">issue a statutory demand</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/wind-up-a-company-that-owes-you-money\" title=\"take out a winding up petition\">take out a winding up petition</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/claiming-money-or-property-from-dissolved-company/buying-a-dissolved-companys-assets","slug":"buying-a-dissolved-companys-assets","order":3,"title":"Buying a dissolved