ing together people owed money (creditors) and hold meetings where necessary</li>\n  <li>decide which creditors should be paid first</li>\n  <li>interview the directors and report on what went wrong in the business</li>\n  <li>get the company removed from the Company Register</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>In a creditors’ voluntary liquidation, the liquidator acts in the interest of the creditors not the directors.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Find a liquidator</h2>\n\n<p>You can <a href=\"/find-an-insolvency-practitioner\" title=\"find an insolvency practitioner\">find an insolvency practitioner</a> who is licensed to act as a liquidator.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/liquidate-your-company/what-happens-to-directors","slug":"what-happens-to-directors","order":5,"title":"What happens to directors","body":"<p>When a liquidator is appointed, if you&rsquo;re a company director:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you no longer have control of the company or anything it owns</li>\n  <li>you can&rsquo;t act for or on behalf of the company</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>give the liquidator information about the company they ask for</li>\n  <li>hand over the company&rsquo;s assets, records and paperwork</li>\n  <li>be interviewed as part of the liquidator&rsquo;s report for the Insolvency Service on why the business failed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You may be banned from being a director for 2 to 15 years or prosecuted if the liquidator decides your conduct was <a href=\"http://www.bis.gov.uk/insolvency/Companies/insolvent-companies/what-action-can-be-taken-against-a-director\" title=\"What action can be taken against a director\" rel=\"external\">‘unfit’.</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Reusing company names</h2>\n\n<p>If you were a director of a company in liquidation, you&rsquo;re banned for 5 years from forming, managing, promoting or managing any business with the same or similar name to the company in li